00060  */
00061 typedef enum {
00062     CVMX_PIP_PORT_CFG_MODE_NONE = 0ull,
00063                      /**< Packet input doesn't perform any
00064                                             processing of the input packet. */
00065     CVMX_PIP_PORT_CFG_MODE_SKIPL2 = 1ull,
00066                      /**< Full packet processing is performed
00067                                             with pointer starting at the L2
00068                                             (ethernet MAC) header. */
00069     CVMX_PIP_PORT_CFG_MODE_SKIPIP = 2ull
00070                      /**< Input packets are assumed to be IP.
00071                                             Results from non IP packets is
00072                                             undefined. Pointers reference the
00073                                             beginning of the IP header. */
00074 } cvmx_pip_port_parse_mode_t;

00102 /**
00103  * Tag type definitions
00104  */
00105 typedef enum {
00106     CVMX_POW_TAG_TYPE_ORDERED = 0L, /**< Tag ordering is maintained */
00107     CVMX_POW_TAG_TYPE_ATOMIC = 1L,  /**< Tag ordering is maintained, and at most one PP has the tag */
00108     CVMX_POW_TAG_TYPE_NULL = 2L,    /**< The work queue entry from the order
00109                                             - NEVER tag switch from NULL to NULL */
00110     CVMX_POW_TAG_TYPE_NULL_NULL = 3L/**< A tag switch to NULL, and there is no space reserved in POW
00111                                             - NEVER tag switch to NULL_NULL
00112                                             - NEVER tag switch from NULL_NULL
00113                                             - NULL_NULL is entered at the beginning of time and on a deschedule.
00114                                             - NULL_NULL can be exited by a new work request. A NULL_SWITCH load can also switch the state to NULL */
00115 } cvmx_pow_tag_type_t;
